BT 1 0 0 1 0 98 Tm /F1 10 Tf 12 TL .076273 Tw (Artificial Intelligence \(AI\) and Machine Learning \(ML\) technologies are key to many modern engineering projects due) Tj T* 0 Tw .559672 Tw (to their ability to solve many problems that are difficult or impossible with other methods. While most engineers will) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.181506 Tw (find themselves enjoying a significant overlap between these techniques and their existing skill set, they are also) Tj T* 0 Tw .429732 Tw (liable to find that AI and ML is its own field with its own unique demands and \(often hidden\) pitfalls. While there are) Tj T* 0 Tw .426123 Tw (many resources available for self teaching, it is generally assumed the practitioner is either an absolute beginner to) Tj T* 0 Tw .0521 Tw (engineering, or already a seasoned expert in AI and ML. In this document, we provide a practical guide to AI and ML) Tj T* 0 Tw 2.467756 Tw (for electronic systems engineers who already have a strong base of knowledge in electronic systems but no) Tj T* 0 Tw .131417 Tw (specialized expertise. This guide will be practice focused, with the goal of helping engineers to make good decisions) Tj T* 0 Tw (and avoid problems.) Tj T* ET
