BT 1 0 0 1 0 74 Tm /F1 10 Tf 12 TL .695256 Tw (Documentation should follow standard best practices. This is quite a large topic that has been extensively covered) Tj T* 0 Tw .059163 Tw (elsewhere \(e.g. Write The Docs\), that we won\222t repeat in this guide. Instead, we devote this section to discussing the) Tj T* 0 Tw 2.34315 Tw (additional considerations required for documentation of data. Documentation for data serves not just a similar) Tj T* 0 Tw .671794 Tw (function to documentation for code in terms of bringing clarity and transparency to what has been done, but it also) Tj T* 0 Tw .03377 Tw (has a strong role in ensuring reproducibility. In many cases, and especially when dealing with challenging data \(such) Tj T* 0 Tw .234952 Tw (as data involving human factors\), how you went about collecting this data is just as important as what you ultimately) Tj T* 0 Tw (collected. Ultimately, we suggest that documentation for data should consider the following three things:) Tj T* ET
